				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Soloing Phinny<a name="29173"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 21 04 10:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Several posts have said that soloing Phinny at 65 is easy.  I'm gonna give it a try, but have a few questions.
<br />

<br />
Do you fight him right in his lair?  One post said to con all the seahorses to see which ones can see invis, implying that not all can.  They you drop into the pit in his lair by one that doesn't see invis.  Is that right?  Once at the bottom and fighting Phinny, will the seahorses attack, or are they out of aggro range?
<br />

<br />
I assume I should start the fight by sucking his mana dry with Lost Composition.  Right?  Can I alternate mez and Lost Composition and drain him without waking him up?  Believe it or not, I've never used mana drain on a mezzed mob, so I'm not sure if it wakes 'em up or not.
<br />

<br />
While meleeing him, I will have to stop the fight periodically to heal up.  How fast does he heal?  I am not elemental.  Will I have a problem killing him this way?  Once he's drained can I just chant kite him around the bottom of his lair and avoid the whoel melee damage issue?
<br />

<br />
Any advice is appreciated.  Thanks!
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Toccata Phantasia
