			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing Phinny<a name="29254"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 21 04 11:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did most of this just the other day.
<br />

<br />
I did the con'ing to make sure Phinny didn't cast see invis on a seahorse, and basically fought him right at or on his platform. The guards do not assist, maybe if somehow you get Phinny really near them. I did not drain his mana. For me, the nukes that randomly hit and if they did were never over 600hp it seemed, were better then his melee on me. He didn't heal but maybe 1% during my mez/heal time. However, at 49% he shot back to 52% fast somehow. Never figured it out, because my wizzy friend came, chain nuked while I chained mez'd. 2 nukes, maybe 3.. Phinny died.
<br />

<br />
Phinny did resist me often at level 65, I started to keep Harmony of Sound on him while 65 mez'ing, to keep safe during my low hp times. Normally, I stopped meleeing and mezed him when my health was below 50% to be safe, so around 30-40% I would get mez to land. He dispells constantly, so ignore buffing up. I could take him down about 10% before I had to stop and mez him. Maybe a little less at first, due to his rune-style spell.
<br />

<br />
This was all done with really... really bad gear, trust me... I still have a Ry'Gorr piece somewhere on me, and gothic steel... at level 65 =/
<br />

<br />
I debated on mana draining, but was too tense to swap a song out. He does summon, so when you mez and are a bit far for his taste, be ready. After a few.... learning expirences in PoN at level 64, I became use to this.
<br />

<br />
An EB item is a must... threw that in just for the sake of making sure. Again, your probably better off finding a high wizard if you can, and chain mez + chain nuke. Maybe tank him some mez heal and then do it, just so Phinny doesn't summon the wizard too fast, and gives a bit more time for the nukes.
<br />

<br />
Always remember to RoT him. Slows make a big difference, you don't need to reslow during a fight, because you'll probably mez him and heal before 1 min is up.
<br />

<br />
This was slow and tedious to me, so be patient and expect to have a good half hour probably, on your side.
<br />

<br />
ps, just saw the chant kite thing... eh, no... he summons<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Also, I wouldn't trust the agro radious of the horses that much.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">- Vaelsu Twostep, Bard of the Legion of Legend on Kane Bayle.</span></td>
